  <prompt>
    <goal>Create docs/architecture/configuration-architecture.md — document the 17 options classes, validators, runtime config, and appsettings hierarchy</goal>
    <context>The BFF API uses the .NET Options pattern extensively with 17+ strongly-typed options classes, FluentValidation-based validators, and a layered appsettings hierarchy (base → environment → local). No architecture document captures this configuration system end-to-end.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Use /docs-architecture skill structure
      - Source ALL content from actual code — do not invent configuration that doesn't exist
      - Document every Options class with its section path, properties, and validator
      - Map the appsettings hierarchy: appsettings.json → appsettings.{env}.json → appsettings.local.json
      - Include runtime config resolution for client-side (Code Pages, PCF)
      - Cite source files for every Options class and validator
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/skills/docs-architecture/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Configuration/</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Options/</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/appsettings.json</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read .claude/skills/docs-architecture/SKILL.md for mandatory structure</step>
    <step>Inventory all Options classes in src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Options/ and Configuration/</step>
    <step>Read Program.cs to find all .Configure&lt;T&gt;() and .AddOptions&lt;T&gt;() registrations</step>
    <step>Read appsettings.json and any environment-specific variants for hierarchy</step>
    <step>Identify all IValidateOptions and FluentValidation validators for options</step>
    <step>Search for runtime config endpoints serving client-side configuration</step>
    <step>Draft configuration-architecture.md following skill structure</step>
    <step>Verify every Options class is documented with section path and source file</step>
    <step>Write to docs/architecture/configuration-architecture.md</step>
  </steps>
  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Write</tool>
